  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6590.86 sitting directly between max negative gamma at 6580 (-15.5B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+13.4B), dealers are currently in heavy short gamma territory and likely buying this level as spot hovers near multiple amplifying strikes. The breakout regime with -44B total GEX means dealers will mechanically buy any dips toward 6580/6575 and sell rallies into 6605, creating whippy two-way flow in this tight 25-point range. Key inflection is the 6605 gamma wall - a break above triggers dealer selling pressure, while failure to hold 6580 accelerates dealer buying down to the 6575 level.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile ping-pong action between 6580-6605 with amplified moves on any breakouts.",
